#- The slap crescendo drawing near§0
§0nigh knocked me on my seat in fear!§0
§0But but right behind the closest oak§0
§0cacophonic claps were choked.§0
§0Silence surely should have brought§0
§0relief, and yet somehow did not.§0
§0I gathered strength, looked 'round the 
#- tree,§0
§0No monster waited there for me.§0
§0A puzz'ling man instead there stood§0
§0in purple shorts and green of hood.§0
§0Beneath his soles I saw the source§0
§0of slapping sounds - flip flops of course!§0

