§0§oGads! §0I thought, §0§oHe's cool as fuck§0
§0and like a fool, sat 
#- there dumbstruck.§0
§0"Yo" he spake, in his strange way,§0
§0"who are you? I'm uwuj"§0
§0I harbored no desire to fight§0
§0and endeavored to remain polite§0
§0but boorish, to my greatest shame§0
§0I blurted "what a stupid name"
#- "Ha!" he laughed "Just wait and see§0
§0the other names they have for me"§0
§0My heart, relieved, began to swell§0
§0though I'd been rude, he took it well.§0
§0"If any understand, I will! §0
§0My names are Willy, William, Bill"§0
§0"ah, not quite" said he, sincere.
#- "Oh, dost though mean like 'Shakespeare'?"§0
§0From ear to ear his grin then spread§0
§0half the way to halve his head.§0
§0"A surname is no riddle sir,§0
§0nor worthy of the glee you stir"§0
§0As he laughed I thought him mad§0
§0and made to move around the cad
#- "Wait!" he gasped, "I will explain"§0
§0Marginally, he seemed more sane.§0
§0"My names depend on how you say§0
§0the following: 'wj'§0
§0But be assured, I'll hold no grudge§0
§0if you prefer to say it 'wj'"§0
§0To be clear on what he'd said -§0
§0the letters first, and
#- second: "wedge"§0
§0I paraphrase to make the rhyme§0
§0but both he said at the same time!§0
